Chairman of the Senate Committee on FCT, Senator Dino Melaye (APC,Kogi) has  narrated how he was arrested at the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja this morning. In a phone interview, Melaye who was declared wanted last month by the Police in a phone interview said he was on his way  to Morocco when he was arrested. " I was at the Airport lounge when they called me that my attention was needed by the officials of the Immigration. When I got there, they told me I'm under arrest on the request of the  Police, " he said. He said the Immigration officials showed him an instruction on his arrest. Melaye who spoke to our corresponded  by 7.50am said that he was still at the airport in the custody of the Immigration officials. He said he was on his way to Morocco for an official engagement sponsored by the federal government.